Compiller make directory input and output near binry file.
you must add to input file: YOUR_NAME.csv and config.csv (config.csv may be only config.csv, not somethin another name)
in config.csv you need write 1) readint_time (MS) 2)write_time (MS) 3) move_time (MS) 4) longMoveTime (MS) 5) (Ram Limit (MB))
in YOUR_NAME.csv (source file) you need write numbers (for example: "1,2,46,74,8" or another)
when you start program you need to put in colsole name of input file "YOUR_NAME.CSV". and after, write output "result.csv" or another.
After program succesfull ended, in output directory you will see result file with sorted numbers.
Temporary files stored in tech directory while runtime, after temporary files will deleted. You cannot rename temporaryFiles.
